@darkled this task is yours, please help (see our key [principles of work](http://www.xdsd.org/2014/04/17/how-xdsd-is-different.html)). If you have any technical questions, don't hesitate to ask right here

The budget of this task is **30 mins**. This is exactly how much time will be compensated, when the task is completed. Read about our [Definition of Done](http://www.xdsd.org/2014/04/15/definition-of-done.html)
@darkled just a reminder that you're working with this task for 12 days already... -30 added to your rating, current score is: [+90](http://www.netbout.com/b/35091?open=rating)
@dmarkov please, assign this task to someone else

> @dmarkov please, assign this task to someone else

@darkled no problem, I'll try to find somebody else

@darkled the task is overdue, and I have to re-assign it to someone else. Please, stop working with it immediately. In general, we're against overdue tasks, check [this page](http://www.xdsd.org/2014/04/13/no-obligations-principle.html)... -60 to your rating, your total score is [-135](http://www.netbout.com/b/35091?open=rating)
@dmarkov @yegor256 I am not sure these -60 are correct, since I've rejected the task 3 days ago, aren't they?

@aoxa this ticket is yours now, please proceed, and keep in mind [this](http://www.xdsd.org/2014/04/17/how-xdsd-is-different.html). Any technical questions you should ask right here... The budget of this task is **30 mins**. This is exactly how much time will be compensated, when the task is completed. Read about our [Definition of Done](http://www.xdsd.org/2014/04/15/definition-of-done.html)
Could you please provide more information as to how to reproduce this? I'm still new to the project and will need more data to solve some issue, but will try to get up to speed asap.

@aoxa the task is your hands for the last 15 days.. keep in mind that if it's not closed in the next 48 hours, it will be re-assigned to someone else, see [No Obligations](http://www.xdsd.org/2014/04/13/no-obligations-principle.html) principle. [This article](http://www.yegor256.com/2015/01/15/how-to-cut-corners.html) should help if you're stuck... added -30 to your rating, now it is equal to -240
